verbs.description: outcheat (third-person singular simple present outcheats, present participle outcheating, simple past and past participle outcheated)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To exceed in cheating; to cheat more than.
examples: In fact, when the definition of infidelity includes not only “sexual intercourse” but also romantic involvement, kissing, and other sexual contact, female college students significantly outcheat their male counterparts.
